Kodiak Capital Group, LLC - PRINCIPALS






















 







































HOMEAPPROACHTRANSACTIONSTEAMPRINCIPALSADVISORY BOARDGENERAL COUNSELNEWSEVENTSAFFILIATESINTERMEDIARIESCONTACT






 Ryan Hodson, Managing Director
Mr. Hodson’s credentials include raising capital and advising clients for Laidlaw & Co in private equity and hedge fund investments. His broad-based career spans
the capital markets as a commodities trader for Iowa Grain, a financial analyst for Lincoln Financial and most recently Managing Director of New York Consulting Group - a private equity fund
specializing in special situations investments. Mr. Hodson brings an arsenal of strategic relationships to Kodiak. His years of Regulation D investing and experience in the broader capital markets
afford him a unique skill set in identifying key investment opportunities for Kodiak. Mr. Hodson attended Becker College and Bentley University and earned his degree in business administration with a
concentration in finance.  


 Colin Manners, Director
 
Mr. Manners is focused on sourcing and evaluating investment opportunities across a wide variety of sectors; maintaining and developing relationships with investment banks and our portfolio
companies is his specialty. He brings international business and marketing knowledge to Kodiak via a decade of experience with Australia’s leading finance bible, The Australian Financial Review.
Prior to The Australian Financial Review he spent over a decade with The News Corporation. Mr. Manner’s formerly represented the USA Rugby League team and is a Director of the American National Rugby
League.  


 Angela Marich, Administrator﻿
 
Ms. Marich has a unique background in the Life Sciences and SAAS industries with a concentration on Global Operations Management, Strategic Planning and Solution
Implementation. Her achievements are based from a sincere passion for business success, a very strong work ethic, and leading exceptional teams toward clear objectives.  She supports the
activities of Kodiak’s investment professionals and assists our LPs and portfolio company executives as necessary.  Ms. Marich believes that our team-orientated culture is the key behind making
challenging projects and deadlines achievable.  






 


 







 







 







 




















